{"type":"message","id":"04ef5e5b","parentId":"06b75087","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:08:25.938Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4bnkgf59i3k1_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"rtk hermes agent token savings tool github\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 893,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"819e20be6304ef63\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - ogallotti/rtk-hermes: RTK plugin for Hermes — rewrites shell ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"819e20be6304ef63\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/ogallotti/rtk-hermes\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4e517e7ef1d581da\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRTK Plugin for Hermes rtk-hermes is a small Hermes Agent plugin that rewrites terminal commands through RTK before execution. Instead of letting Hermes run verbose shell commands directly, the plugin asks rtk rewrite for a lower-context equivalent: ... RTK then returns filtered output to the LLM, which usually means fewer tokens in the context ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4e517e7ef1d581da\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f2840998680d5e2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - ogallotti/rtk-hermes: RTK plugin for Hermes — rewrites shell ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0f2840998680d5e2\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://t.co/mnRxGj8Z9b\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"42f6d80315f7cb08\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe plugin registers a pre_tool_call hook that intercepts terminal tool calls. When the agent runs a command like git status, the plugin delegates to rtk rewrite which returns the optimized command (e.g. rtk git status). The compressed output enters the agent's context window, saving tokens . All rewrite logic lives in RTK itself ( rtk rewrite).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"42f6d80315f7cb08\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"t.co\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d230fd5087278173\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRTK Documentation | RTK\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d230fd5087278173\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.rtk-ai.app/docs/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"13ce63c19d638faf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWhat RTK optimizes Dozens of commands across all major ecosystems — Git, Cargo/Rust, JavaScript, Python, Go, Ruby, .NET, Docker/Kubernetes, and more. See What RTK Optimizes for the full list with savings percentages.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"13ce63c19d638faf\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.rtk-ai.app\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a1e3dbaaa63a0d70\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRTK (Rust Token Killer): Reduce LLM Token Consumption by 60-90% with ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a1e3dbaaa63a0d70\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://pyshine.com/RTK-Rust-Token-Killer-LLM-Optimization/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6deecf93f290aa7b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nLearn how RTK (Rust Token Killer) reduces LLM token consumption by 60-90% on common dev commands. This single Rust binary transparently filters and compresses command outputs before they reach your AI coding agent's context window.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6deecf93f290aa7b\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"pyshine.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"43339877cad57860\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\ntokscale — Hermes Agent Developer Tools | Hermes Atlas\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"43339877cad57860\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://hermesatlas.com/projects/junhoyeo/tokscale\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1e87600c617af3d1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe tool supports a wide range of integrations including Hermes Agent , Claude Code, OpenClaw, and GitHub Copilot CLI. Tracks token usage and costs across multiple AI coding agents\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1e87600c617af3d1\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"hermesatlas.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"rtk hermes agent token savings tool github","provider":"duckduckgo","count":5,"tookMs":893,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"duckduckgo","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"819e20be6304ef63\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - ogallotti/rtk-hermes: RTK plugin for Hermes — rewrites shell ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"819e20be6304ef63\">>>","url":"https://github.com/ogallotti/rtk-hermes","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4e517e7ef1d581da\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRTK Plugin for Hermes rtk-hermes is a small Hermes Agent plugin that rewrites terminal commands through RTK before execution. Instead of letting Hermes run verbose shell commands directly, the plugin asks rtk rewrite for a lower-context equivalent: ... RTK then returns filtered output to the LLM, which usually means fewer tokens in the context ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4e517e7ef1d581da\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0f2840998680d5e2\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - ogallotti/rtk-hermes: RTK plugin for Hermes — rewrites shell ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0f2840998680d5e2\">>>","url":"https://t.co/mnRxGj8Z9b","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"42f6d80315f7cb08\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe plugin registers a pre_tool