/tokscale","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1e87600c617af3d1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe tool supports a wide range of integrations including Hermes Agent , Claude Code, OpenClaw, and GitHub Copilot CLI. Tracks token usage and costs across multiple AI coding agents\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1e87600c617af3d1\">>>","siteName":"hermesatlas.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778404105938}}
{"type":"message","id":"1be53f5e","parentId":"04ef5e5b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:08:36.959Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"rtk-hermes is a plugin for Hermes specifically. My setup uses OpenClaw, not Hermes. But wait - let me check my actual setup. The user uses OpenClaw and Hermes. Let me check if Hermes is running and if rtk is available there.\n\nBut actually, looking at the MEMORY.md - I don't think rtk is something that's currently set up. And I should first ask the boss before touching Hermes-related things (per the hard rules).\n\nLet me think about this:\n1. rtk = Rust Token Killer - rewrites shell commands to use compressed equivalents\n2. rtk-hermes is a plugin specifically for Hermes\n3. But the user's main setup uses OpenClaw\n\nThe user asked if I can use it. Let me check if rtk is available on the Hermes side and if it would work with their setup. But first I need to read the hermes-permission skill since touching anything Hermes-related requires explicit permission.\n","thinkingSignature":"bdd974027c54c0b1b3100bdceba7d5d4b6844bbaedcd208c3bb86e869f922b05"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ev486dhd19l2_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace/skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1306,"output":245,"cacheRead":31552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33103,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778404105940,"responseId":"064f7e0acb822cf15ef70472ea259ffe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"00c1df4d","parentId":"1be53f5e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:08:36.984Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ev486dhd19l2_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: hermes-permission\ndescription: Require explicit user permission before doing anything related to Hermes Agent, including reading, inspecting, configuring, restarting, editing, diagnosing, running commands, services, files, skills, memory, gateway, logs, or any other Hermes-related action. Use whenever a task mentions Hermes, hermes-agent, ~/.hermes, hermes-gateway, Hermes skills, Hermes config, Hermes service, or Hermes troubleshooting.\n---\n\n# Hermes Permission\n\nBefore doing any Hermes-related action, ask the user for explicit permission first.\n\nThis applies to all Hermes-related work, including:\n\n- Reading or inspecting files under `~/.hermes`\n- Running `hermes ...` commands\n- Checking, starting, stopping, restarting, or inspecting `hermes-gateway.service`\n- Editing Hermes config, skills, memory, profiles, logs, sessions, plugins, gateway settings, or service files\n- Diagnosing, troubleshooting, migrating, updating, uninstalling, or backing up Hermes\n- Using tools to search, index, analyze, or summarize Hermes files or code\n\nDo not treat \"look\", \"check\", \"diagnose\", \"summarize\", or \"ทำความรู้จัก\" as permission. Ask first.\n\nSafe response pattern:\n\n```text\nขออนุญาตก่อนครับเจ้านาย งานนี้เกี่ยวกับ Hermes ให้ผมดำเนินการได้ไหมครับ\n```\n\nProceed only after the user clearly approves in the current conversation.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778404116984}}
