{"type":"message","id":"78b93e64","parentId":"bd1756a0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:17:13.227Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q6quma6f1ulh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Service]\n# Keep Telegram downtime short after crashes/restarts.\nRestartSec=30\nRestartSteps=0\nRestartMaxDelaySec=10\n\n# SocratiCode MCP sometimes leaves npm/node children behind on gateway restart.\n# Clean them so the next gateway start does not spawn duplicates or hang shutdown.\nExecStopPost=/home/apinan/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh\nTimeoutStopSec=150\nWatchdogUSec=0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":20,"aggregated":"[Service]\n# Keep Telegram downtime short after crashes/restarts.\nRestartSec=30\nRestartSteps=0\nRestartMaxDelaySec=10\n\n# SocratiCode MCP sometimes leaves npm/node children behind on gateway restart.\n# Clean them so the next gateway start does not spawn duplicates or hang shutdown.\nExecStopPost=/home/apinan/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh\nTimeoutStopSec=150\nWatchdogUSec=0","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778404633227}}
{"type":"message","id":"f038c16e","parentId":"78b93e64","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:17:24.445Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the override has RestartSec=30 and RestartSteps=0 with RestartMaxDelaySec=10. Let me check what the restart policy is - it might have Restart=always or something.\n\nThe status shows \"deactivating (stop-sigterm)\" - so the service is currently stopping, not stuck. It might have been triggered to restart by someone (Mes_bot) and is now in the process of stopping.\n\nWait - Mes_bot ran `systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway` and the service is now \"deactivating (stop-sigterm)\" - this means the restart command was issued and the service is being stopped. The issue is it says \"Gateway shutting down — Your current task will be interrupted\" which is a message from the gateway itself.\n\n\nLooking at the systemctl output, the main PID is still 163587 with many child processes running, and it's been in a deactivating state for almost 2 minutes now. The ExecStopPost cleanup script is what I should investigate next.\n","thinkingSignature":"076a7ee428a9a47b9782d6d3e84c100598973e7b57b66b1f3d9754b2939ac1f8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l1lj07py8ivp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/apinan/.hermes/bin/cleanup-socraticode.sh 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":213,"output":248,"cacheRead":37504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778404633228,"responseId":"064f801a6b7b0d278d691b99eb91397f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0dee4ab3","parentId":"f038c16e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:17:24.472Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l1lj07py8ivp_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -u\n\nPATTERN='npm exec socraticode|sh -c socraticode|node .*/socraticode($| )|node .*/node_modules/.bin/socraticode($| )'\n\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n# First try graceful termination.\nkill -TERM $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nsleep 5\n\n# Force-kill anything still alive (including orphaned npm/node children of socraticode).\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -n \"$pids\" ]; then\n  kill -KILL $pids 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 2\nfi\n\n# Extra sweep: kill any leftover node/npm processes that were children of socraticode\n# These survive when the parent python dies but the stdio child escapes the cgroup.\nleftover=\"$(pgrep -f 'node.*socraticode|npm.*socraticode|node.*mcp-server' -u \"$USER\" || true)\"\nif [ -n \"$leftover\" ]; then\n  kill -KILL $leftover 2>/dev/null || true\nfi\n\nexit 0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -u\n\nPATTERN='npm exec socraticode|sh -c socraticode|node .*/socraticode($| )|node .*/node_modules/.bin/socraticode($| )'\n\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\n# First try graceful termination.\nkill -TERM $pids 2>/dev/null || true\nsleep 5\n\n# Force-kill anything still alive (including orphaned npm/node children of socraticode).\npids=\"$(pgrep -u \"$USER\" -f \"$PATTERN\" || true)\"\nif [ -n \"$pids\" ]; then\n  kill -KILL $pids 2>/dev/null || true\n  sleep 2\nfi\n\n# Extra sweep: kill any leftover node/npm processes that were children of socraticode\n# These survive when the parent python dies but the stdio child escapes the cgroup.\nleftover=\"$(pgrep -f 'node.*socraticod