{"type":"message","id":"ac95103d","parentId":"afeba1ee","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:23:42.744Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found it! The process running `systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway` is actually a child of hermes-gateway itself! It's in `/tmp/hermes-snap-b391a3eae002.sh` - this is a hermes snapshot script that's running the restart command.\n\nSo Mes_bot is actually running inside Hermes as a tool/script. Looking at the path `/tmp/hermes-snap-b391a3eae002.sh` - this is a temporary script created by Hermes itself. This means Mes_bot isn't a separate process - it's integrated INTO Hermes somehow, likely as a tool or automation script that's being triggered.\n","thinkingSignature":"244337b5b2795e4b2376b0a1c8310d24ed39ad8d7839fc02c211546bf0a2ab3e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n🧑🏼‍💻 เจอแล้ว! **Mes_bot อยู่ใน Hermes เอง** — มันเป็น automation script ที่รันอยู่ภายใน gateway\n\nจาก log: `/tmp/hermes-snap-b391a3eae002.sh` → มันเป็น **snapshot script** ที่ Hermes สร้างขึ้น ไม่ใช่ process แยก\n\n**วิธีแก้:** ผมจะสร้าง override ให้ systemd ไม่ restart hermes-gateway อัตโนมัติ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je5mwomphx14_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user/hermes-gateway.service.d && cat > ~/.config/systemd/user/hermes-gateway.service.d/no-auto-restart.conf << 'EOF'\n[Service]\n# Prevent auto-restart loops from external triggers\nRestart=no\nEOF\nsystemctl --user daemon-reload && systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway && echo \"Done\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":427,"output":399,"cacheRead":43584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44410,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778405003799,"responseId":"064f818c8e090c5864d58d184f858719"}}
