{"type":"message","id":"a6e3a654","parentId":"d1cd4266","timestamp":"2026-05-10T09:43:34.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss wants me to set up RTK hooks to work automatically. The warning said \"No hook installed — run `rtk init -g` for automatic token savings\". But the thing is, RTK init is for Claude Code, and for OpenClaw it's different - hooks don't auto-apply. \n\nBut let me try to set up something that makes rtk run automatically. The issue is that OpenClaw's exec tool doesn't have a hook system like Claude Code does. \n\nOne approach: I could try to set up a wrapper or alias at the shell level so that git/ls/find commands automatically go through rtk. But that's risky because it could break things.\n \nI found the OpenClaw skill already exists at `~/.openclaw/skills/rtk-integration/SKILL.md` with the core rule to always prefer RTK versions. Since OpenClaw doesn't support hook auto-application for exec commands like it does for Claude Code, I'll need to rely on explicitly using `rtk` prefixes for shell commands instead. I could try wrapping common commands through a shell alias or function in the user's bashrc, though this approach has limitations with complex commands. For OpenClaw specifically, the skill documentation explicitly states that hooks don't auto-apply and that `rtk <cmd>` needs to be used directly rather than attempting some workaround.\n\nThe most practical solution here is to add rtk as a prefix to commands through bashrc aliases—making git map to rtk git, ls map to rtk ls, and so on. This way when OpenClaw's exec tool runs these commands, they'd automatically be routed through rtk. However, this is risky since it could interfere with other commands that aren't compatible with rtk.\n","thinkingSignature":"c7fa0eb4e64ec46fddfa5f20fdee1d904a31596b3ceacfb5cf4613233d405603"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ay58h9g99037_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.bashrc 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"rtk\\|alias\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":833,"output":402,"cacheRead":61184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62419,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778406193834,"responseId":"064f863329945d0085e9d11de884baed"}}
